items.name: MORE-Q
items.description: Repo for MORE-Q(X) dataset and MORE-ML machine learning framework

items.name: iris-streamlit
items.description: This project is a Machine Learning web application built using Streamlit that predicts the species of an Iris flower based on user-provided measurements.  The application demonstrates how a trained ML model can be quickly deployed as an interactive web app using pure Python, without any frontend frameworks.

items.name: Urban-Sustainability-Indexing-Global-City-Clustering-for-Green-Futures
items.description: Unsupervised machine learning and geospatial analytics framework for clustering global cities based on sustainability, ESG, infrastructure, and climate-resilience indicators to support smart-city planning and public-policy decision modeling.

items.name: QuantTradeAI
items.description: A comprehensive machine learning framework for quantitative trading strategies

items.name: NErlNet
items.description: Nerlnet is a framework for research and development of distributed machine learning models on IoT

items.name: MultiScaleArrays.jl
items.description: A framework for developing multi-scale arrays for use in scientific machine learning (SciML) simulations

items.name: SIGMA
items.description: SIGMA (Smart Intelligent Grid Management Architecture) .SIGMA is an AI framework designed to bring intelligence, resilience, and automation to modern power grids. This project integrates simulation data, machine learning models, and realtime monitoring pipelines to detect, classify, and respond to faults across multiple layers of the grid.

items.name: quantum
items.description: An open-source Python framework for hybrid quantum-classical machine learning.

items.name: Credit-risk-desicion-support-system
items.description: Developing an automated credit risk management framework, integrating high-performance machine learning and an algorithmic bias control mechanism.

items.name: aiko_services
items.description: Distributed service framework using asynchronous messages supporting IoT, Machine Learning and Video

items.name: AB-TRAP
items.description: This is a five-step framework for the development of intrusion detection systems (IDS) using machine learning (ML) considering model realization, and performance evaluation.

items.name: sesethunkqenkqa.github.io
items.description: Audit AI models for fairness and explainability with VeritasAI, the ethical framework for responsible machine learning training and evaluation.

items.name: HackGpt
items.description: HackGPT Enterprise is a production-ready, cloud-native AI-powered penetration testing platform designed for enterprise security teams. It combines advanced AI, machine learning, microservices architecture, and comprehensive security frameworks to deliver professional-grade cybersecurity assessments.

items.name: NbSi-ML-Design
items.description: Interpretable machine learning framework for designing Nb-Si based ultra-high temperature alloys with enhanced fracture toughness (>20 MPam^1/2)

items.name: RainML-daily--Reconstruction
items.description: Python-based multi-stage framework for daily rainfall time-series reconstruction in seasonal tropical forest ecosystems using unsupervised anomaly detection, bias-corrected reanalysis and satellite data, and multi-objective machine learning selection.

items.name: On-chip-ML-simplified
items.description: Basic on-chip machine learning framework for System-on-Chip (SoC) FPGAs using Direct Memory Access.

items.name: IndustrialSolarML
items.description: Industrial Data-Driven Machine Learning Framework for Wafer Quality-Based Decision Making toward Smart Solar Cell Manufacturing

items.name: mirna-candidiasis-bioinformatics
items.description: Bioinformatics and Machine Learning framework for in silico prediction of candidiasis-related microRNAs. Includes data processing, feature engineering, and ML models for miRNA-disease association prediction.

items.name: RTL-Timing-Prediction-Machine-Learning-Framework-for-VLSI-Design-Automation
items.description: A machine learning framework to predict VLSI circuit delays from RTL metrics. Using 20 designs and ensemble techniques, it achieved 3.28% MAPEfar better than the 10% target. The system integrates multiple models, Bayesian optimization, SHAP explainability, delivers a production API with 12ms latency and 90% confidence intervals.

items.name: folax
items.description: Folax (Finite Operator Learning with JAX) is a framework for solving and optimizing PDEs by integrating machine learning with numerical methods in computational mechanics.

items.name: awesome-agentic-machine-learning
items.description: A curated list of awesome agentic machine learning projects, frameworks, and resources.

items.name: insider-threat-dashboard
items.description: This project provides a robust, machine learning-driven framework for identifying potential insider threats within an organization's digital ecosystem. The system analyzes user behavior, network activity, and data access patterns to proactively flag suspicious activities.AI Explainable Alerts and Role-Based Explanations

items.name: ModelTrace
items.description: A Research-Grade Framework for Inspecting, Debugging, and Stress-Testing Machine Learning Models

items.name: spiking-learn
items.description: Framework for machine learning with spiking neural networks

items.name: A-hybrid-physics-driven-machine-learning-ML-framework-for-modeling-confined-fluid-density
items.description: The framework of this hybrid physical-driven ML approach. The core idea is to leverage the prior physical model of corr to define a meaningful input descriptor space and output target, while using ML to identify and quantify the residual physics not captured by the prior model.
